sec.p:
Heterozygous SNPs were identified using GATK (see above). This set of SNPs was then filtered to remove low quality or unreliable genotype calls by discarding SNPs that:
failed QC after GATK quality recalibration (as described above);
were heterozygous in less than 2 donors;
were homozygous in less than 2 donors;
showed allelic imbalance in input (‘non-ChIPed’) DNA at nominal p-values <0.05.
